metadata.name: Composition #3 #27
metadata.description:
A composition in 3D space of pseudo-architectural elements. 
If you think about it, you can recognize architectural details - used in a decontextualized way - typical of Louis Kahn, Aldo Rossi, Mies van der Rohe, of Italian Rationalism and even a little of the style of Fortunato Depero.
Through interaction it is possible to manipulate the point of view to discover all the details of this postmodern composition. 
All the elements were created through the code.

metadata.name: Urban Agony #24
metadata.description: Today your love visited the agonizing city and solved nothing. You must understand that the world never plays the same, and only ashes remain of the soul you had to break.

metadata.name: Imaginary Dawn Rev2 #12
metadata.description:
A generative artwork created by Zydron especially for fxhash. The last work for the fxhash genesis collection.

Layers of overlapping textures merge and create an imaginary dawn. 5 color palettes.



Uma obra de arte generativa criada por zydron especialmente para o fxhash. 

Camadas de texturas sobrepostas se fundem e criam um alvorecer imaginário. 3 paletas de cores.

metadata.name: Colorfall #69
metadata.description:
My first attempt at a generative NFT. This started with an idea to create a grid of diagonal lines with the basic line function of p5js. I had discarded this idea until my friend said it looked like a waterfall of colors and he liked it, so I decided to mint it. After tweaking some parameters like colors and line thickness it produced some nice outputs.

I hope you will enjoy it. Free mint(unless you cant wait and want to pay =) plus 25% royalties for minters.

reserves for the collectors of my testnft on objkt, my friend CampendonkP and a few artists who I remembered who did free mints, like punevyr and JohnRising.
